<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rapids 2, Wizards 1, SO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Wolde Harris tied the game in regulation and then  
scored in the shootout to help the Colorado Rapids to a 2-1 victory 
over winless Kansas City on Saturday night in the MLS. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris converted a penalty kick in the 69th minute to tie the  
score 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado (2-2) earned the penalty kick after Wizards defender  
Uche Okafor was whistled for a handball as he deflected a cross 
that Harris was lining up for a side volley. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris was one of three Rapids to score in the shootout, while  
Colorado goalkeeper Marcus Hahnemann stopped three of the Wizards' 
attempts. 
</P>
<P>
	Rapids defender Matt McKeon score the deciding goal and Joey  
DiGiamarino also converted. 
</P>
<P>
	Chris Brown and Vicente Figueroa had shootout goals for Kansas  
City (0-5). 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards scored in the 30th minute when Alexi Lalas converted  
the rebound of a shot by Brown. Former Rapids midfielder Chris 
Henderson assisted on the play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
