<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Two Drown After Boat Is Swamped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOORE HAVEN, Fla. (AP) -- Two men drowned after their small  
fishing boat was swamped by the wake of passing cabin cruisers, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses said none of the four people aboard the 15-foot bass  
boat were wearing life jackets during their Friday afternoon ride 
in the Caloosahatchee River, near Lake Okeechobee. 
</P>
<P>
	The boat's owner, Cleveland Burkett, 65, had taken three  
passengers out for an impromptu trip after noticing his craft was 
sitting crooked on its trailer, said Jim Huffstodt, a spokesman for 
Florida Game and Freshwater Fish Commission. 
</P>
<P>
	The wakes from the two passing crafts threw the group into the  
river, where Burkett and passenger James Isenberg, 57, drowned. 
</P>
<P>
	Burkett's wife and Isenberg's fiancee were unhurt and were able  
to swim to shore. 
</P>
<P>
	The couple was engaged to be married on Wednesday.  
</P>
<P>
	Investigators have interviewed the captain of one of the passing  
boats but have not identified the other craft. 
</P>
<P>
	The river is part of the Intracoastal Waterway connecting Fort  
Myers to Stuart. 
</P>
</TEXT>
