<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nashville Signs Top Pick Legwand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- The Nashville Predators signed their  
first-ever draft pick, center David Legwand, to a contract on 
Saturday and planned to put him in the lineup against the New 
Jersey Devils Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deal were not disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	Legwand, selected second overall in the 1998 draft, played in  
three preseason games with the Predators before he was returned to 
the OHL's Plymouth Whalers. The Whalers were knocked out of the OHL 
playoffs on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-1, 180-pound Detroit native led the Whalers with 54  
goals and 51 assists in 59 games. He was named the OHL's rookie of 
the year and MVP after the 1997-98 season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
