<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Vikings' Thomas Accused of Assault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CROWLEY, La. (AP) -- Minnesota Vikings free safety Orlando Thomas  
was arrested Friday night after his wife accused him of assaulting 
her, authorities said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas, 26, was booked on a charge of domestic violence after  
his arrest at 11:30 p.m., according to a press release issued by 
Acadia Parish Sheriff Kenneth Goss. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas' wife was treated at a local hospital and released. The  
statement did not give her name or any specifics about her 
injuries. Thomas was held briefly at the Acadia Parish Jail until 
he posted bond. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas was born in Crowley and owns a home in the town, which is  
140 miles west of New Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
	The Vikings re-signed Thomas, their starting free safety, to a  
four-year contract worth $11 million in February. The deal includes 
a $2.75 million signing bonus -- most of it deferred -- and incentive 
money aimed at improving Thomas' workout habits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
