<HEADLINE> Washington Times Changes Sundays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- No more leafing through the paper to get those  
Saturday scores for readers of The Washington Times. Starting 
Sunday, the sports section comes first. 
</P>
<P>
	In a ``letter from the editor'' in Friday's newspaper, editor in  
chief Wesley Pruden said the outside of Sunday editions will now be 
the new Sunday Sports Times. 
</P>
<P>
	Sports editor Gary Hopkins said, ``We've always been known for  
politics, national issues, trends, things like that. We were 
looking for something unique. Sports is big. When you think about 
what happened Saturday, what are people going to the Sunday paper 
for?'' 
</P>
<P>
	``The entire sports section will be the `A' section,'' he said,  
nearly double the size of the Times' normal Sunday sports sections. 
</P>
<P>
	Inside will be the regular Sunday paper, ``a convenient pull-out  
section with the usual front page of The Times,'' Pruden said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
