<HEADLINE> Swingin On Ice Wins at Keeneland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Swingin On Ice remained undefeated in  
three starts by winning the $135,350 Grade II Beaumont Stakes in 
record time Saturday at Keeneland. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden for the first time by Robby Albarado, the daughter of El  
Prado caught pacesetter Secret Hills with less than a furlong 
remaining and pulled away to a two-length victory. 
</P>
<P>
	Time for the seven furlongs, 184 feet on a fast track was 1:25  
3-5, 2-5 of a second faster than the stakes record held by Golden 
Gale. 
</P>
<P>
	Secret Hills led from the start, increasing her lead to 1 1/2  
lengths at the top of the stretch, but had to settle for second, 3 1/2 
lengths in front of Appealing Phylly. 
</P>
<P>
	Confessional, winner of the Grade I Frizette Stakes as a  
2-year-old and the 7-10 favorite, finished sixth in the field of 
seven 3-year-old fillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Don Amos and trained by Josie Carroll, Swingin On Ice  
picked up $83,917 for the victory, increasing her career earnings 
to $122,317. She won races at the Fair Grounds in her two previous 
starts. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner paid $13.20, $6.60 and $5.40. Secret Hills returned  
$8 and $6.60, while Appealing Phylly paid $5.20 to show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
