<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Former Mets GM Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JENSEN BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Joe McIlvaine, former general manager  
of the New York Mets and now an assistant GM for the Minnesota 
Twins, was charged with a misdemeanor for nude sunbathing on a 
public beach. 
</P>
<P>
	McIlvaine, 51, was arrested last Monday after Martin County  
sheriff's deputies answered several calls complaining about a man 
lying on his stomach on the beach without any clothes on. 
</P>
<P>
	``It looks like he had to have known better,'' said Janell  
Atlas, spokeswoman for the sheriff's office. ``He knew he wasn't 
supposed to be naked. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was lying there buck naked,'' Atlas said. ``When the deputy  
approached him, he started to put his shorts back on.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McIlvaine was released on $1,000 bail.  
</P>
<P>
	McIlvaine's lawyer, Michael Rubin, called it ``not a big deal at  
all.'' He said McIlvaine thought he was on a private beach, and 
therefore not violating any rules. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a real innocent incident of sunbathing,'' he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
