<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Davenport To Miss Fed Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- With Lindsay Davenport out with a wrist  
injury, the United States turned to Monica Seles to lead it in the 
first round of the Fed Cup against Croatia this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	Seles, who was born in Novi Sad, Yugoslavia, wasn't even slated  
to be on the U.S. team. But when the series was moved from Zagreb, 
Croatia, to Raleigh because of NATO airstrikes over Yugoslavia, 
U.S. captain Billie Jean King added Seles. 
</P>
<P>
	International Tennis Federation officials also decided against  
playing the series in Hamburg, Germany, where Seles was stabbed 
during a match nearly six years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	``She is playing great,'' King said Friday. ``And she's getting  
better and better. So she's back in a big way.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Seles' Bausch &AMP; Lomb Championships title last weekend was her  
first since last September. 
</P>
<P>
	Ranked third in the world, one spot below Davenport, Seles will  
play in the second match today against Croatia's Silvija Talaja, 
who is undefeated in five Fed Cup singles matches. 
</P>
<P>
	During a ceremonious draw on the lawn outside the North Carolina  
governor's mansion, Iva Majoli, the top-seeded player on the 
Croatian team, was chosen to play Chanda Rubin in today's opening 
match. 
</P>
<P>
	Davenport, who lost to Anna Kournikova in two sets in the Bausch  
&AMP; Lomb last weekend, was forced to drop out of the Lipton 
Championships earlier this spring because of her sprained left 
wrist. She decided Wednesday her wrist was not well enough to play. 
</P>
<P>
	``(Davenport's injury) doesn't have much of an impact,'' King  
said. ``The U.S. is lucky to have great depth ... We have Monica 
and Chanda.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The four Croatian women and their captain said they were excited  
to be playing in Raleigh, with or without Davenport, who said she 
hopes to recuperate in time for the French Open. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a big thing for Croatia,'' said Majoli, who has played  
in the last seven Fed Cups. ``We should just enjoy the weekend.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But Majoli, who has been beaten Davenport four times in their  
eight meetings, said Davenport's injury ``is a disappointment.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Her captain, Vjeran Friscic, however, seemed pleased with the  
draw. 
</P>
<P>
	``Frankly, I prefer Chanda, but all the players are top and  
everyone knows how to play well,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Rubin leads the head-to-head series with Majoli 3-2, winning in  
three sets at the Hopman Cup in 1997. Both players are coming off 
three-set losses in the Baush &AMP; Lomb. 
</P>
<P>
	``I haven't played Chanda in so long. It's going to be a tough  
match,'' Majoli said. 
</P>
<P>
	The players switch opponents Sunday. The series ends with a  
doubles match pitting Seles and Lisa Raymond against Majoli and 
Talaja to determine which team advances to the second round. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
